<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French President Sends Message to Mubarak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Visiting French Defense Minister
Alain Richard today conveyed a message from President Jacques
Chirac to Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak.
</P>
<P>
Chirac expressed France's firm support for Mubarak's initiative
aiming at patching up the disrupted Mideast peace process in the
verbal message, the top French military official said following a
meeting with Mubarak at the Mediterranean port city of Alexandria.
</P>
<P>
France considers Egypt's policy very successful in this
connection, he told reporters, adding that the message also dealt
with the strong relations binding Cairo and Paris in various
fields.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Egyptian Defense Minister Hussein Tantawi told
reporters that the French guest's trip here is aimed to launch
closer cooperation between the two countries' defense ministries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to set up a joint committee responsible
for exploring prospects for military cooperation, he said.
</P>
<P>
The French defense minister and his accompanying delegation
arrived here Friday on a four-day official visit to Egypt at the
invitation of Tantawi.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers co-chaired a session of Egyptian-French talks
on military cooperation, training, armament and exchange of
expertise in the Egyptian Ministry of Defense headquarters earlier
today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is a follow-up to their meetings in Paris last
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
