<HEADLINE> India's Bihar State Government to Seek Trust Vote </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Rabri Devi, whose appointment as
India's Bihar chief minister has drawn flak across the country,
today decided to seek a trust vote in the state assembly on
Monday, three days after her surprise elevation to the post, Press
Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
Devi, wife of former Bihar chief minister Laloo Prasad Yadav,
succeeded her husband on Friday after his resignation over his
alleged involvement in a multi-crore rupee embezzlement scandal in
the state.
</P>
<P>
As a housewife without any political experience, Devi's
elevation has triggered widespread controversy in the country.
</P>
<P>
She was accused of heading a proxy government of his
scandal-tainted husband.  
</P>
</TEXT>
