<HEADLINE> Hun Sen Meets Chinese Businessmen, Stresses One China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 16 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia resolutely upholds the
"one China" policy and will only develop economic relations with
Taiwan, Cambodian Second Prime Minister Hun Sen said today during
a meeting with some 600 Chinese businessmen in the capital.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister paid tribute to these business
representatives from Chinese inland areas, Hong Kong, Taiwan and
Macao, saying they have made great contributions to the
development of Cambodian economy.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen said that Cambodia recognizes the government of the
People's Republic of China as the sole legitimate government of
China and Taiwan is but part of China.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that his country will never establish political
relations with Taiwan, saying it is a matter of principle
concerning state sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the closing of Taiwan's trade and cultural office
in Phnom Penh earlier this week, Hun Sen said it is part of
Cambodia's efforts to solve its security and political problems.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he expressed his hope that the move would not affect
normal Taiwanese investment in Cambodian.
</P>
<P>
The interests of Taiwanese businessmen should be protected by
the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
