<HEADLINE> Alonso to Face Dewulf in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Spanish Julian Alonso set up a
final match with Belgian Filip Dewulf after beating Slava Dosedel
of Czech 6-3, 6-4 to reach his first ATP Tour final at the
Generali Open on Saturday at Kitzbuehel, Austria.
</P>
<P>
The 19-year-old Alonso took the match pace to make a quick 5-1
lead before he won the first set.
</P>
<P>
He broke a good start in the second half, while the 15th seed
Dosedel wavered 2-2. But he didn't sustain his power and lost his
serve at 4-3. Alonso took his two services to win the set.
</P>
<P>
Alonso won two challenger tournaments in 1997 in Venice and
Contrexville. Earlier this year, he made the third round at Key
Biscayne by defeating Steve Bryan and Tim Henman in the second
round in Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
In Sunday's final, will meet 10th-seeded Belgian and French
Open semifinalist Filip Dewulf, who had little trouble defeating
Spaniard Galo Blanco 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Dewulf, who recorded his only tournament win at the 1995 hard
court CA-Trophy in Vienna, had an easier task against French Open
quarter-finalist Blanco.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian, who has not lost a set here, needed a single break
at 2-0 to take the first set, and breaks at 1-0 and 5-2 to enter
his first final of 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
