<HEADLINE> Olano Wins 20th Stage of Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Abraham Olano of Spain won the
63-kilometer individual time-trial 20th and penultimate stage of
the Tour de France on Saturday at Marne La Vallee, France.
</P>
<P>
Olano, who has struggled to fill the shoes of legendary
compatriot Miguel Indurain in this year's race, clocked 1 hour 15
minutes 57 seconds, 45 seconds faster than German Jan Ullrich.
</P>
<P>
Ullirich may be the first German to win the Tour. But he took
nothing for granted for his victory over French Richard Virenque
until after Sunday's final, who is led by the yellow-jersey-wearer
by over nine minutes.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's final stage takes the riders 149.5km from Disneyland
to the Champs Elysees in Paris. 
</P>
</TEXT>
