<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan Condemns Israel's New Settlement Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 26 (Xinhua) - The Jordanian government here today
condemned an Israeli plan to build a new Jewish settlement in Arab
east Jerusalem as another violation of its peace deal with the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"The Jordanian government rejected and condemned such decisions
and warned the danger in implementing such settlement," Nasser
Lawzi, acting Minister of State for Information Affairs, read a
statement after a regular cabinet meeting.
</P>
<P>
Israel`s Jerusalem municipal authority Thursday authorized a
American Jewish millionaire to build 70 Jewish homes in the heart
of the Arab neighborhood of Ras el Amud of east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
This was the second time this year that Israel made such
decisions. The first was in March which has put the peace process
into an impasse.
</P>
<P>
The building of the new Jewish settlement would further
escalate tensions which have been high since Israel broke ground
for the controversial Har Homa settlement in March, said Lawzi.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian government believed that Israeli moves like these
violated the terms of the Middle East peace process, he added.
</P>
<P>
The government called on the Israelis to cancel these decisions
and stop building settlements on any Palestinian land occupied by
Israel.
</P>
<P>
Jordan helped mediate the Israeli-Palestinian Hebron accord in
January on Israeli pullout from Hebron and West Bank. 
</P>
