<HEADLINE> TAZARA Launches Marketing Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzania-Zambia Railway
Authority (TAZARA ) has launched an aggressively marketing drive
in Zambia, South Africa and the Democratic Republic of Congo, the
Zambia News agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency quoted TAZARA Director for marketing
and traffic Joseph Minsula as saying today in the Tanzanian
capital Dar es Salaam that the marketing strategy involves
sensitising staff on the needs of customers.
</P>
<P>
The strategy includes a managerial information system to
facilitate tracking of cargo on all routes, Minsula said.
</P>
<P>
The marketing program also entails increasing cooperation
between the company and the Tanzaian Harbors Authority to service
the Dar es Salaam Corridor more efficiently.
</P>
<P>
He told TAZARA will by September purchease six locomotives
to improve its performance.
</P>
<P>
The production of TAZARA has been on decline in the last few years.
It transported 636,000 tons of cargo in 1995 compared to 662,000
tons of cargo it transported in 1994. 
</P>
