<DOCNO> XIE19970727.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Defense Minister to Visit Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 26 (Xinhua) -- French Defense Minister Alain
Richard will arrive in Saudi Arabia Sunday on a two-day official
visit that would focus on defense cooperation between the two
countries and French arms sale to the kingdom.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here today said Richard is expected to hold
lengthy talks with his Saudi counterpart Prince Sultan Bin Abdul
Aziz to tackle bilateral military and defense cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The sources close to the French embassy in Riyadh said that
France had signed a deal for the supply of arms and military
instruments to Saudi Arabia worth 3.8 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
They said the talks would likely touch upon a French desire to
sell 250 tanks to Saudi Arabia against stiff competition from the
United States and Britain.
</P>
<P>
They also revealed that France had received a Saudi request to
purchase a third French frigate worth 1.133 billion dollars. The
kingdom received two French frigates last April as part of a deal
signed in 1994 to the tune of two billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
France has been a major arms supplier to the oil-rich Saudi
Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Prince Sultan visited France last March at the invitation of
President Jacques Chirac, on way back home from a visit to the
United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
