<DOCNO> XIE19970727.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-26 20:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Inaugurates Giant Oil Refinery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani tonight inaugurated a giant oil refinery with an
investment of 1.5 billion U.S. dollar and 1.6 billion rials
(500,000 dollars) in souther port of Bandar Abbas.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA said that the refinery is one
of the biggest in the world and the 8th in Iran. It has been
constructed on a 700-hectare plot of land about six kilometers
from the Persian Gulf coast.
</P>
<P>
IRNA said that it is considered one of the most modern oil
installations using sea water in its cooling system which is
recyclable without causing any environmental complications.
</P>
<P>
The refinery meets all modern specifications in matters of
energy conservation, safety, adaptability and international
standard compatibility, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
It took five years to complete the project with a capacity of
refining 232,000 barrels of oil per day. The major products will
consist of liquid gas, gasoline, jet fuel, kerosene, tar, sulphur
and other petroleum by-products.
</P>
<P>
The refinery is also expected to run at the capacity to meet
its domestic requirements in oil in addition to exporting its
various oil products, IRNA added.
</P>
<P>
Iran, the fourth largest oil producer and the second largest
oil exporter in the world, yields 3.6 million barrels per day
(bpd) and exports 2.5 million bpd in accordance with OPEC quota.
</P>
<P>
Iran oil export earnings, which stood at 19.1 billion dollars
last year, accounts for nearly 80 percent of its total export
revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
