<HEADLINE> India to Import Banknotes From U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
authorized the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) to import banknotes of
100-rupee and 500-rupee denominations worth one trillion rupees
(about 28.6 billion U.S. dollars) from the United States to tide
over the country's acute shortage of notes, Press Trust of India
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The cost of the imported notes would be about 95 million
dollars, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the RBI is also setting up two more currency note
printing presses in West Bengal and Karnataka respectively to
alleviate the shortage of banknotes.
</P>
<P>
When fully commissioned by the end of next year, their
production capacity would be nine billion units annually.
</P>
</TEXT>
