<DOCNO> XIE19970727.0031 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Wanda Continues Winning Streak in China Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Dalian Wanda hammered Vanguards
Huandao 3-1 in a 12th-round match on Sunday, extending its
unbeaten record to 46 at the China Professional Soccer League.
</P>
<P>
With this home-match victory, Dalian led the standings at 32,
well ahead of the second-placed Beijing Guo'an, at 20.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, which went down twice to the Vanguards in this year's
China Football Association Cup, took the advantage throughout with
their fierce attacks.
</P>
<P>
Dalian opened the scorings in the 31st minute through Li
Min. Four mintues later, Wang Tao added the second with a header,
making Dalian leading 2-1 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
The home team kept its momentum in the second half while Li
scored another goal on a close-range pass from his teammate Hao
Haidong in the 56th minute. It was Li's sixth goal this season.
</P>
<P>
Taking advantage of the loose defense of Dalian, Wu Wenbin
pulled one goal back for Vangurds just before the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
1995 China Soccer League champion Shanghai Shenhua, dying for a
victory to stop the recent slump, suffered another blow as
Shanghai went down to Yanbian Aodong 0-1.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, which was surprisingly beaten 1-9 by Beijing Guo'an
in the 10th round, collected only three points out of the recent
seven league matches.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an beat Sichuan Quanxing in their away-match 2-0
and moved up to the second place in the standings, followed by
Qingdao Hainiu.
</P>
<P>
In the other matches of the day, Qingdao Hainiu defeated Jinan
Taishan 1-0, Tianjin Samsum and August First played to a 1-1 tie
while Guangdong Hongyuan edged Guangzhou Apollo 1-0. 
</P>
