<HEADLINE> Nepali Couple Made Outcasts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A newly-wed couple and their
family members have been made social outcasts by their community
in southern Nepal simply because they are brother and
sister-in-law, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Barun Kumar Chaudhari, a villager living in Mahottari district,
recently challenged his community by marrying his widowed
sister-in-law.
</P>
<P>
This daring act was hailed by the press as a brave step towards
reforming the existing social malpractice and countering the
practice of dowry.
</P>
<P>
However, the marriage drew widespread wrath from the community
elders.
</P>
<P>
They prevented a priest from performing the marriage ceremony,
and called a village meeting announcing that the Chaudharis will
not be allowed any longer to participate in any social rituals and
festivals, the reports said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
