<HEADLINE> Beijing Reports Favorable Financial Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital city reported
a stable financial situation and a brisk financial market during
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics from the Beijing branch of the People's Bank
of China, the central bank, showed that the deposits with the
city's financial organizations topped 478.11 billion yuan at the
end of June, up 33.64 billion yuan from the year's beginning.
</P>
<P>
The deposits with the banks increased 31.23 billion to 419.76
billion yuan during the period, up 21.3 percent from the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Individual savings deposits rose 9.15 billion to 178.95 billion
yuan, up 18.3 percent on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Loans extended during the period registered marked growth, with
the outstanding bank loans climbing 14.54 billion yuan from the
year's beginning to 205.26 billion yuan, an increase of 4.1
billion on an annual basis.
</P>
<P>
Medium- and long-term loans grew by 3.4 billion yuan, mainly
granted to the city's infrastructure sector.
</P>
<P>
The financial market was active during the period, as was
partly indicated in a stunning securities turnover, which topped
288.177 billion yuan during the January-May period.
</P>
<P>
More than 80.9 billion yuan was raised at the city's
fund-raising center, up 41.7 from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The insurance market continued to expand, as the premium income
rose 23.3 percent on an annual basis to 2.49 billion yuan at the
end of May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
