<HEADLINE> UAE Oil, Gas Production Rises in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates' oil
output reached 117.3 million tonnes in 1996 while that of natural
gas topped 35 billion cubic meters, said a latest energy report
reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
These indicate a 3.2 percent increase in oil output as against
113.7 million tonnes in 1995, and a 17 percent hike in natural gas
as compared with 29.9 billion cubic meters in the previous year,
said the Statistical Review of World Energy 1997.
</P>
<P>
As the world's top seven oil producers, the UAE has the world's
fourth largest proven oil reserves of 97.8 billion barrels by the
end of 1996, or 9.4 percent of the world's total of 1036.9 billion
barrels.
</P>
<P>
The Gulf country is also abundant in natural gas deposits with
its proved gas reserves reaching some 5,800 billion cubic meters,
according to the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
