<HEADLINE> China Ensures Protection of Foreign Economic Interests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 27 (Xinhua) -- China pledged
today that legitimate economic and trade interests of foreign
countries in Hong Kong will be protected.
</P>
<P>
The pledge was given by Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen during his meeting with Canadian Foreign
Minister Lloyd Axworthy here this evening, a spokesman for the
Chinese Foreign Ministry said at a news briefing after the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Qian said "Hong Kong, after its return to China, will surely
remain stable and prosperous" and believed that the wide-ranging
economic and trade links between Canada and Hong Kong would be
further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the two ministers expressed their
satisfaction with the recent development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese minister said contacts and cooperation in various
fields between China and Canada have developed smoothly, there has
been frequent exchange of visits and consultations have been
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Qian hoped that with joint efforts, the cooperative
relationship between China and Canada would reach a new high.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy, who congratulated China on its resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong, said Canada attaches great
importance to its relations with China and wishes to work together
with China to expand the areas of bilateral cooperation for the
benefit of both sides, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers also discussed international issues such as
the U.N. affairs and shared the view that the two countries can
develop consultations, dialogue and cooperation at multilateral
forums.  
</P>
