<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Stresses Sustained Agricultural Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Jiang Chunyun has
stressed that every possible effort must be made to increase
farmers' incomes and maintain sustainable agricultural development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made this remark during a tour from July 23-27 in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, a major grain producer.
</P>
<P>
He called on localities to study the new situations and solve
problems that are arising in rural areas after two years of
harvests.
</P>
<P>
Special attention should be paid to improving rural industrial
structures and farm produce mix, and opening up more channels for
the distribution of farm products, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Priority must be given to developing viable crops which will
bring more revenue to farmers, he said.
</P>
<P>
He strongly emphasized the need to develop the service sector
in rural areas in order to link production with processing and
sales.
</P>
<P>
Above all, steps must be taken to protect farmers' enthusiasm,
improve the household contract responsibility system, lighten
farmers' financial burdens, and promote the democratic elections
in rural areas, Jiang concluded. 
</P>
</TEXT>
