<HEADLINE> American Students Doing Environmental Survey In Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Eighteen teachers and students
from the Abraham Lincoln High School in Philadelphia are working
on a joint environmental research project with their Chinese
counterparts in Tianjin, a major port city in North China.
</P>
<P>
The American teachers and students are inspecting and analyzing
the water quality of the Haihe River, which runs through Tianjin,
in an attempt to discover ways to clean up the river.
</P>
<P>
Liu Wenqiang, deputy director of the Tianjin Environmental
Protection Bureau, said that the one-week summer camp was
organized to improve the young people's awareness of environmental
protection.
</P>
<P>
"Young people, wherever they are from, have a responsibility to
protect the earth," Liu said.
</P>
<P>
Last year, middle school students from Beijing, Shanghai,
Tianjin and eight other cities visited the United States, studying
environmental protection together with American students. 
</P>
