<HEADLINE> Large Bridge to Be Built Over Haihe River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- North China's port city Tianjin is
to cooperate with a Hong Kong firm to build a 2,500-meter-long
cable bridge over the Haihe River.
</P>
<P>
The bridge, to be built at the Haihe River's mouth on the Bohai
Sea, will be erected 37.5 meters above water.
</P>
<P>
Hong Hong's China Construction Holdings Ltd. will finance the
bridge construction at a cost of 600 million yuan (about 72
million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The new bridge will be the largest on the river.
</P>
<P>
The mouth of the river is both the base of the Bohai Oilfield,
China's first offshore oilfield, and the site of China's largest
manmade port, the Tianjin New Harbor.
</P>
<P>
Traffic jams of up to several hundred meters are now common
in the area near the mouth of the Haihe River; about 100,000
vehicles pass by there daily.  
</P>
</TEXT>
