<HEADLINE> Guangxi Records Steady Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Expanded economic reform fueled
steady economic growth in the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
during the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Period statistics show that the region's gross domestic product
jumped 8.8 percent on the previous year's period to end at 85.9
billion yuan (10.7 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Guangxi's agricultural sector has also witnessed healthy
development, a trend most likely to continue. The regional
government plans to increase spending on agricultural
infrastructure construction by 24 percent to 120 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The region's farmers planted over 26.45 million mu (1.76
million ha.) of spring grain crops, up more than 480,000 mu on
1996. Projections call for the summer grain output to reach 8.95
billion kg, up 300 million kg. on the year before.
</P>
<P>
The region's total industrial output value for the first six
months hit 107 billion yuan, up 9.8 percent on the 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi has also witnessed steadily increasing revenue, with
the 6.28 billion yuan recorded in the first six months
representing a 14.1 percent rise on the l996 period. Total
outstanding deposits for the region's financial institutions
approached 147.2 billion yuan by the end of June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
