<HEADLINE> East China Regulates Brand Tea Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Tea lovers warmly welcomed 1997
production figures showing a 2,000 kg output for Biluochun, a
famous Chinese green tea produced in Wuxian, eastern Jiangsu
province.
</P>
<P>
Biluochun, one of the top ten brands of Chinese green tea grown
in the Dongting Mountain near Wuxian, is known for its delicate
leaves, shape, pure color, condensed fragrance, and lasting taste.
</P>
<P>
Producers have been forced to warehouse authentic Biluochun
tea in recent years due the volume of counterfeit products
flooding the tea market.
</P>
<P>
Wuxian called on the Jiangsu Bureau of Technological
Supervision to help curb the situation by establishing a
"Biluochun Tea Quality Exemplary Zone", with related plans
currently on the agenda of the State Bureau of Technological
Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The provincial bureau issued its Biluochun tea standards in
February 1997, and the Wuxian government has established "Ten
Standards" governing areas such as purchases, quality control,
packaging and ensuring the authenticity of Biluochun
labels. Wuxian has also enlisted experts to verify the quality of
Biluochun and has introduced various laws to protect the local
brand.  
</P>
