<HEADLINE> Public Library Helps Tibetan Cultural Research </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Tibet Library, which opened to
the public in the capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region last
July, has made an effort to develop itself into a place for the
study of Tibetan culture and traditions.
</P>
<P>
It now has nearly 600,000 books in its collection, and will
serve as a center to protect the rare cultural heritage of the
Tibetan people, according to its curator, who noted that the
popular notion that Tibetan culture is likely to be wiped off the
face of the earth is nonsense.
</P>
<P>
