<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong elderly people
dependent on social welfare are likely to receive an allowance for
their social life, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
The allowance was under consideration in an effort to improve
the living standard of the old people who rely on the
Comprehensive Social Security Assistance of 2,060 HK dollars (266
U.S. dollars) a month, today's newspapers quoted an official of
the Special Administrative Region (SAR) government as saying.
</P>
<P>
