The amount of the allowance has not been settled, but details
will be announced by Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa in his policy
speech in October, said Fok.
</P>
<P>
Welfare for the elderly has become a social concern in Hong
Kong since one in every ten local residents was aged 65 or above
in 1996. Hong Kong's population reached 6.4 million at the end of
last year.  
