<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Company Bankruptcy Under One Percent of Newly Founded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The total number of new court
insolvency in Hong Kong rose moderately between January and June
this year compared with the same period of 1996, the latest
government statistics show.
</P>
<P>
Official Receiver Robin Hearder said today that new insolvency
cases, including both company and personal bankruptcy, reached 601
in the first six months of this year, a moderate increase of 11
percent from the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
There were 280 new compulsory company liquidation orders from
January to June. But corporate failure was still less than one
percent of the new companies incorporated during the same period,
said the official.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, 31,188 new companies were
registered.
</P>
<P>
Company bankruptcy mainly affected such businesses as garment
and knitting, trade, restaurants and canteens, construction and
engineering, and electronics.
</P>
<P>
The majority of claims against individual bankruptcies were
guaranteed debts and consumer credit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
