<HEADLINE> South China Encouraging Spending On Science, Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangzhou, the
capital of Guangdong province, has been encouraging research
institutes and enterprises to increase spending on science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Spending in that field has been growing at an annual rate of 20
percent, and stood at 3.5 billion yuan (440 million US dollars)
last year.
</P>
<P>
The city government has asked enterprises to spend more than
one percent of sales on technological development, and hi-tech
firms to spend over five percent.
</P>
<P>
To encourage firms to increase spending, the city has said that
enterprises that increase spending on technological development at
an annual rate of more than 10 percent will enjoy favorable tax
policies.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou also provides loans for technology projects related
to its backbone industries, and plans to increase spending on
science and technology to more than three percent of its budget
for the year 2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
