Commission of Liberia formally announced the results of last
Saturday's election Friday in Monrovia, in a meeting with the
political parties.
</P>
<P>
It declared that Taylor's National Patriotic Party won 75
percent of the total votes cast, far ahead of all the other 12
candidates.
</P>
<P>
In the parliamentary election held simultaneously, Taylor's
party also won 21 out of the 26 seats in the Senate and 49 out of
the 64 seats in the House of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prince Yommie Johnson, leader of a faction of
Taylor's National Patriotic Front-line during the civil war, has
said that he expects to play a key role in Taylor's government.
</P>
<P>
Johnson said this in Lagos in an interview with a Nigerian
newspaper last week.
</P>
<P>
Taylor is expected to be sworn in as the new Liberian
president on August 2. 
