<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eight Killed in Belgian Air Show </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 27 (Xinhua) -- A Jordanian aircraft crashed on
Saturday during a stunt maneuver at an air show held in Belgium,
killing eight people and injuring more than 40, a dozen of them
seriously, radio reports said today.
</P>
<P>
The plane suddenly went out of control when it was making a
dive. It smashed into the ground near a public grandstand at the
Ostende airport at 5:00 p.m., sending debris and flames that
caused the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Six of the dead have been identified. They are the Jordanian
pilot described as being "well-experienced", and two French and
three Belgian spectators.
</P>
<P>
The specific cause of the incident is still under
investigation. But local reports said that the plane might have
been pushed by a gust of air current and then lost balance.
</P>
<P>
The injured were immediately rushed to hospitals in the cities
of Ostende, Gand and Brussels. So far, 37 of them remain in
hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Belgian King Albert II and the Queen cut short their holidays
in Italy at the news and returned to visit the injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
