<P>
PETALING JAYA, Malaysia, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign
Minister Yevgeny Maksimovich Primakov today spoke highly of the
contributions made by Russia and China to the peace and security
in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The positive and dynamic development of Russian-Chinese
relations "has made an impressive contribution to the cause of
peace and security in the Asia-Pacific region," Primakov said at
the fourth ASEAN Regional Forum meeting held here this morning.
</P>
<P>
He said the Joint Declaration on a Multi-Polar World and
Formation of a New International Order signed by Russian President
Boris N. Yeltsin and Chinese President Jiang Zemin on April 23
this year in Moscow represents a powerful statement of the two
countries "in favor of establishing a new world order based on
equitable cooperation and account of the interests of each other
as well as those of the rest of the world."
</P>
<P>
"The document underlines that Russia and China firmly support
the idea that mutual respect for sovereignty and territorial
integrity, mutual non-aggression, mutual non-interference in
internal affairs, equality and mutual benefit, peaceful
coexistence and other generally accepted rules should become the
basis of a new international order," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is fully in keeping with the principles of cooperation
within the ARF, and effectively constitutes an important
confidence-building measure taken by two major forum participants
of their own free will," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Russian foreign minister said that another example of the
practical movement towards the implementation of real
confidence-building measures was provided by the recent agreements
between five Asian nations, namely Russia, China, Kazakhstan,
Kirgizstan and Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
After signing the Agreement on Confidence-Building in the
Military Field in the Border Area in Shanghai in April last year,
the five countries' leaders signed on April 24 this year in Moscow
a more far-reaching document -- the Agreement on the Reduction of
Armed Forces in the Border Area, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said "these two obligations objectively have established in
Asia a vast area of stability along the borders stretching for
over seven thousand kilometers."
</P>
<P>
"This is a good example of how stronger security in the region
can been attained through confidence building in the military
field and genuine arms cuts," he added.
</P>
<P>
The one-day ARF meeting is being attended by the foreign
ministers from the nine members of the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN), 10 ASEAN dialogue partners including China.
The Cambodian foreign minister and the special envoy of the
foreign minister of Papua New Guinea are also present at the ARF
meeting as observers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
