<HEADLINE> Iran to Issue New ID Cards to Foreign Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran is to issue new identity cards
for over 2 million foreign refugees in the country, today's local
Persian daily Iran quoted Interior Minister Ali Mohammad Besharati
as saying.
</P>
<P>
It said that Besharati revealed the plan in an address to a
conference of the directors of the Interior Ministry's aliens
bureau in Mashhad, the capital of the northeastern province of
Khorassan.
</P>
<P>
