<HEADLINE> Two Quakes Shake Iran's Ancient City of Shiraz </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Two earthquakes measuring 4.0
and 4.9 degrees on the open-ended Richter scale hit Iran's
ancient city of Shiraz, 920 kilometers south of Tehran, today.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that the two quakes
occurred at 04:19 and 06:29 hours local time today.
</P>
<P>
The seismological base of Shiraz, which is affiliated to
Geophysics Institute of Tehran University, registered the
epicenter of the first quake at 50 kilometers south of the base
in Kuar district.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the second tremor was registered at Dasht-e
Arzhan, 35 kilometers west of Shiraz.
</P>
<P>
No report has yet been received on possible damage inflicted
by the tremors. 
</P>
