<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Falls Further </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- India's annual rate of inflation
fell further by 0.27 percentage points to touch 4.43 percent for
the week ended July 12, the lowest in the past one year, Press
Trust of India said today.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the inflation to fall below the
five-percent-mark since last July.
</P>
<P>
Compared to this, inflation was at 5.88 percent in the
corresponding week last year.
</P>
<P>
The official wholesale price index (WPI) for "all commodities"
(base 1981-82=100) rose 0.1 percent to 325.2 during the week under
review as against 325.0 the week before.
</P>
<P>
Prices of commodities such as raw cotton and mustard seed moved
down during the reference week.  
</P>
</TEXT>
