<HEADLINE> Tension Grips Dhaka University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Tension is prevailing on the campus
of Bangladesh's most famous Dhaka University, following an
indefinite strike call from today by a students group of the
opposition Bangladesh Nationalist Party (BNP).
</P>
<P>
The Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal (JCD) has called the strike
protesting the "capture" of Surya Sen Hall by activists of
pro-government Bangladesh Chhatra League (BCL) and the
authorities' "failure" to rehabilitate JCD activists in the hall.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, the BCL members captured the Surya Sen Hall, a
strong hold of the JCD, after two factions of the JCD clashed each
other over establishing supremacy at the hall earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
The JCD leaders also announced a five-day program beginning
today which included a student strike in the educational
institutions all over the country on July 29 in support of their
demand.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, the university authority decided to postpone
all examinations scheduled for July 27 and 28. Fresh dates for the
postponed examinations would be announced later, said a press
release of the university.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a large number of policemen have been posted at the
hall gates and adjoining areas to avert any untoward incident.
</P>
