<HEADLINE> 2 Italian Tourists Gunned Down at Chiang Mai Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Two Italian men were seriously
wounded Saturday afternoon at Chiang Mai Airport when a gunman
opened fire on a group of tourists waiting to board a plane.
</P>
<P>
The two victims, Sanna Franco, 43, and Rigattieri Franscesco,
27, were in critical condition at a Chiang Mai hospital last
night, the local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
Sanna was hit in the right arm and left shoulder while
Rigattieri was hit in the right cheek with the bullet passing
through his neck.
</P>
<P>
The gunman, wearing a motorcycle helmet and dressed in military
trousers and a dark jacket, had walked up to the group of Italians
and shot them without warning. He then fled on a motorcycle.
</P>
<P>
Chiang Mai is a most popular tourist destination in north
Thailand. The accident could further adversely affect Thailand's
tourism industry following a big hotel fire earlier this month in
Pattaya which killed 91 people.
</P>
<P>
After questioning witnesses, police believe the gunman was
Rungroj Somjai, an immigration police officer who was transferred
to Chiang Mai from the south a week ago after tourists complaints
against him.  
</P>
</TEXT>
