<HEADLINE> Inner Mongolia Imports Canadian Livestock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 27 (Xinhua) -- More than a thousand head of
Canadian purebred cattle were brought to the Xilin Gol pastures of
the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region recently as the beginning of
a co-operative project to import 10,000 head of Canadian livestock
by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
The northern Chinese region has agreed with Canada to spend 30
million yuan on the first phase of a purebred beef cattle base,
says Zhao Houquan, deputy general manager of the Inner Mongolia
Chuangye Group.
</P>
<P>
The Canadian side will also provide fine grass seed, barley,
equipment, and embryo transfer and frozen semen technology.
</P>
<P>
The imported cattle can gain as much as 500 kg in a year and a
half and the beef sells well in Southeast Asia.  
