<HEADLINE> Latin American Cultural News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The following are news briefs
about cultural events taking place in Latin American countries in
the last few days:
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Some 600 professional clowns attended Mexico's
10th National Clowns Meeting from July 22 to 24 in Puebla City,
the capital of the state of Puebla.
</P>
<P>
The participants discussed topics including guidelines for
clowns associations, legal counseling, labor contracts, and modern
comicity techniques.
</P>
<P>
The gathering aimed to compile a national clowns directory and
to exchange experiences among the professionals.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- The First Meeting of Schools of Dance was held from
July 24 to 26 in Chile.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Karen Konnolly School of Dance, the meeting
included roundtable discussions, workshops, classes, visits to
museums and presentations.
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Shakira, of Colombia, is scheduled to arrive here on
August 2 to offer for the first time a sole concerto of "Pub
Victoria" at the Grandshaw Stadium of Managua.
</P>
<P>
Shakira, 20, started her artistic career at five and has an
distinctive flair for songs and dances of her Arab ancestry.
Shakira is an Arab name that means "woman full of grace".
</P>
<P>
Her last album "Bare Feet" has been a great success.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Spanish tenor Placido Domingo will offer two
concerts at the Colon Theater here, marking the 25th anniversary
of his debut at the theater.
</P>
<P>
Domingo, to be joined by Argentine Mezzosoprano Cecilia Diaz,
will play the main role of "Sampson and Delila," of Camille
Saint-Saens, on July 30 and August 2.
</P>
<P>
The first time Placido Domingo sang at the theater was in 1972,
when he was 31.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The first film out from Mercosur countries,
jointly produced by Argentina, Brazil and Uruguay, has finished
the production process recently.
</P>
<P>
The film, which tells a story of political struggles in the
borders of the three countries in the 1920s, will be premiered in
Brazil in August and in Argentina and Uruguay in September.
</P>
<P>
Mercosur, the biggest trade bloc in South America, groups
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay. 
</P>
</TEXT>
