Southeast Asian Nations) member countries -- Brunei, Indonesia,
Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and
Vietnam, the two ASEAN observer countries Cambodia and Papua New
Guinea, and the 10 ASEAN dialogue partners -- Australia, Canada,
China, India, Japan, New Zealand, Russia, South Korea, the United
States and the European Union.
</P>
<P>
Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen is heading the
Chinese delegation to the ARF, which was initiated four years ago
with the aim of dealing with issues such as security and stability
in the Asia-Pacific region, global arms control and regional
confidence-building measures.
</P>
<P>
