<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Oil Prices Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 26 (Xinhua) -- The prices of the crude oil
exported by Venezuela dropped from an average of 16.30 dollars per
barrel last week to 15.93 dollars per barrel this week.
</P>
<P>
The Energy and Mines Ministry estimated in its weekly report
that the average price for this month would be 15.85 dollars per
barrel, slightly above the 15.80 dollars per barrel in June.
</P>
<P>
The average, based on the prices of major types of crude from
the country, was 16.70 dollars per barrel in the first six months
of the year, a bit lower than the 16.92 dollars per barrel in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The price of the basket of seven crudes from the Organization
of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) was 17.89 dollars per
barrel this week, against the 18.18 dollars per barrel last week.
</P>
