<HEADLINE> Container Transport Upsurges in Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen, a special economic zone
next-door to Hong Kong, reported a surge in container transport in
the first half year.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show the Shenzhen port handled 471,300 standard
containers in the first six months, a year-on-year rise of 122.1
percent. The cargo handled by the port in the period totaled 15.66
million tons, up 18.2 percent, of which foreign trade-related
cargo volume hit 8.77 million tons, an increase of 13.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local transport expert attributed the upswing to the return of
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"More and more foreign businesspeople are now eyeing Shenzhen,
a port which also boasts fine facilities and is adjacent to Hong
Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
More routes were opened by overseas navigators in the
period. For example, an Israeli state shipment company has started
to run a regular transport route to Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
Also, the increase of foreign trade in Shenzhen brought a
steady supply of commodities to the port.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, Shenzhen now has five harbors for
container transport and runs 13 international ocean-going shipping
routes to different destinations worldwide.  
</P>
</TEXT>
