<HEADLINE> China to Hold Investment and Trade Fair Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation recently announced in Shanghai
that beginning this year, China will hold an investment and trade
fair every year on September 8.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that China has made remarkable progress in
absorbing foreign investment ever since 1979 when the country
started the reform and opening-up drive.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1996, China had approved the establishment of
more than 280,000 foreign-funded enterprises, with promised funds
topping 469 billion US dollars and actual investment hitting 177
billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
By 1996, China had for three consecutive years ranked second as
a leading recipient of foreign investment worldwide, next only to
United States, and was drawing increasing attention from the world
capital markets.
</P>
<P>
Beginning this year, the former Fujian Investment Fair will be
re-named the China Investment and Trade Fair, which will be
co-sponsored by the Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation, the Fujian Provincial Government and the Xiamen
Municipal Government.
</P>
<P>
The organizing committee of the upcoming '97 China Investment
and Trade Fair, scheduled to be held in the Xiamen Special
Economic Zone from September 8-13, has received applications for
registration from nearly 40 provinces, cities and ministries,
which are scheduled to bring with them 1,000 key projects in need
of funding.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 projects are expected to be promoted during the
fair, according to organizers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
