<HEADLINE> Russia to Downsize Government by 10 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Russian First Deputy Prime Minister
Boris Nemtsov today said the federal government has decided to
downsize 10 percent of its payroll list.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov announced the government decision through a hot line
established by the newspaper "Komsomolskaya Pravda", the Itar-Tass
reported.
</P>
<P>
The move, he said, will affect federal government institutions,
ministries and administrative departments.
</P>
<P>
