<HEADLINE> Middle School Students Finish Adventure in Lop Nur Desert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Forty middle school students in
this capital of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region
have just returned from a week-long adventure in the Lop Nur
Desert, known as a former nuclear testing ground of the Chinese
army.
</P>
<P>
Since China announced that it would immediately suspend nuclear
testing a year ago, the former military zone has become an
education center where Chinese students are given education in
patriotism and study the country's national defense system.
</P>
<P>
The 40 students, from all nationalities in the region,
completed the 1,000-km-long tour and camping trip in the desert as
part of the center's summer program.
</P>
<P>
The summer camp was arranged by the city's education
commission, and the city's committee of the Communist Youth
League, as well as other governmental organs.
</P>
<P>
The group visited the desert barracks of the People's
Liberation Army of China, and heard lectures on patriotism from
the soldiers.
</P>
<P>
China launched its first atomic bomb in the desert in 1964.
</P>
</TEXT>
