<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manufacturing Activities in Colombia Down 4.28 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 26 (Xinhua) -- Colombia's manufacturing
activities, excluding coffee threshing, were down 4.28 percent in
the first four months of the year over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sectors with negative growth were lumber and wood furniture,
glassware, printing and publishing, leather products and electric
machinery, said the National Statistics Administrative Department.
</P>
<P>
Other sectors registering reduced production and without signs
of recovery for now were rubber and tire, chemicals, non-metallic
minerals, machinery, earthenware, china ware and porcelain objects.
</P>
<P>
The sales of manufacturing sectors during the four-month period
dropped 3.77 percent if coffee threshing is excluded, and 3.13
percent if it is included, said the government statistics service.
</P>
<P>
If coffee threshing is accounted, said its report available
today, the contraction of manufacturing activities in Colombia was
3.81 percent in the first four month of the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
