<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Philippine Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 27 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Philippine newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
Manila Bulletin
</P>
<P>
-- Philippine President Fidel Ramos promised Saturday a much
better Philippines which he will turn over to his successor on his
"graduation day," June 30, 1998, after six years in office.
</P>
<P>
Today
</P>
<P>
-- Opposition senators in the Philippines will fight new moves
by administration congressmen to convene a constituent assembly to
amend the Constitution in order to extend the term of President
Fidel Ramos, and have linked talk of a brewing Senate coup to such
efforts.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine Journal
</P>
<P>
-- President Fidel Ramos said Saturday that through cooperative
efforts members of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations can
withstand the speculative attacks on their currencies.
</P>
<P>
The Sunday Chronicle
</P>
<P>
-- The Philippine government has basically decided that
Filipino maids working in Malaysia should receive a 50 percent
increase in their minimum wage, a report said Saturday.  
</P>
