<HEADLINE> German House Explosion May Be Deliberate Sabotage: Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 26 (Xinhua) -- A gas explosion that destroyed a
four-story apartment house and killed six people in the western
German city of Duesseldorf Thursday may be deliberate sabotage,
police said today.
</P>
<P>
Investigators found that a cap on a gas pipe in the basement of
the building had apparently been screwed off before the explosion,
the German news agency DPA quoted police sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the landlord of the building and a roofer were
detained by the police Friday in connection with a separate arson
attack one year ago on the same building.
</P>
<P>
Police believed that the two men had conspired to set fire to
the building in March 1996 in order to drive tenants out of the
low-rent flats and rent them at higher prices.
</P>
<P>
But the two men were released by a magistrate today because
there was no sufficient evidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
