<HEADLINE> East China Province Maintaining Steady Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 27 (Xinhua) -- Fujian province's GNP for the first
half of this year was 122.6 billion yuan, up 14 percent
year-on-year, according to the Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
In this east China's province, the primary industries were up
10 percent, secondary industries, 16.6 percent, and the service
sector, 13 percent.
</P>
<P>
Output of primary industries -- agriculture, forestry, animal
husbandry, and fisheries -- totaled 27.3 billion yuan, up 12
percent.
</P>
<P>
The province's county-level companies had 179.8 billion yuan in
output value, up 27.2 percent, and exports of 32.8 billion yuan,
up 30.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector made some progress in the first half with
96.9 billion yuan in output value.
</P>
<P>
The industrial sector had 91.5 billion yuan in sales, up 17
percent, while the accumulated output/sales ratio was 94.4
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
